Program: Crossing Continents
Title: Going Hungry in Venezuela
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b07m7pl0
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 8 Aug 2016
Oil-rich Venezuela is struggling to feed its own people as a result of a spiralling economic and political crisis which has brought the country to its knees. Vladimir Hernandez returns to his home country where thousands queue for many hours in order to buy even the most basic of food stuffs. Malnutrition and starvation, unthinkable only a few years ago, are becoming a reality for some communities and particularly the poor. Show less